s forgetting established workflows, testing procedures, and project-specific conventions.\\\\n\\\\n## Examples of forgotten instructions:\\\\n- Not following the documented testing procedures (e.g., using `nox -s test` vs trying to run pytest directly)\\\\n- Ignoring virtual environment setup instructions\\\\n- Forgetting project-specific commands and workflows\\\\n- Not adhering to contribution guidelines\\\\n\\\\n## Impact\\\\nThis causes developer frustration as Claude Code attempts incorrect approaches that are clearly documented, requiring users to manually remind it to check the README or other documentation.\\\\n\\\\n## Suggested improvements:\\\\n1. Prioritize README.md and CONTRIBUTING.md content in context\\\\n2. Maintain better awareness of project-specific instructions throughout conversations\\\\n3. Check documentation files before attempting common developer tasks\\\\n4. Better retention of project setup and workflow information within a session\\\\n\\\\n## Reproduction\\\\n1. Start a session in a project with clear README instructions\\\\n2. Ask Claude Code to perform tasks like running tests or setting up the environment\\\\n3. Observe that it sometimes attempts generic approaches instead of following documented project-specific instructions\\\\n\\\\nThis issue affects developer productivity and trust in the tool's ability to work effectively within established project structures.\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:core\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe8A\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"memory\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYgjA\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:35Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:36Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017748,\\\"number\\\":16,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Tool Use Sequence Interrupted: Missing Tool Result Block\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nI got claude into a weird state where it quit working. I thought it was maybe an outage or my wifi issues or something so I tried restarting my mac, using different VPNs, and even logging into 3 separate claude accounts. but each time I was using claude -resume and going into that same convo I got the error .   \\\\n At first I was getting different errors, maybe from a wifi or VPN issue. because I use starlink and have been having frequent VERY SHORT outages, like \\\\u003c 1s each. Somehow from me retrying different claude prompts, it got into a weird cycle with that error about tool uses and finally I tried just quitting claude and starting a new context without using -resume.\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: darwin\\\\n- Terminal: Apple_Terminal\\\\n- Version: 1.0.72\\\\n- Feedback ID: c2aec1a9-6adc-42db-bf98-d193be52208c\\\\n\\\\n**Errors**\\\\n```json\\\\n⎿ API Error: 400 {\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"invalid_request_error\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"messages.255: `tool_use` ids \\\\n    were found without `tool_result` blocks immediately after: toolu_015ZXgypVKGqFDCB2TtgNgSA. Each `tool_use` block \\\\n    must have a corresponding `tool_result` block in the next message.\\\\\\\"}}\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:34Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:35Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017587,\\\"number\\\":14,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"[BUG] Maximum call stack size exceeded on first install\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Environment\\\\n- Platform (select one):\\\\n  - [x] Anthropic API\\\\n  - [ ] AWS Bedrock\\\\n  - [ ] Google Vertex AI\\\\n  - [ ] Other: \\\\u003c!-- specify --\\\\u003e\\\\n- Claude CLI version: 1.0.72 (Claude Code)\\\\n- Operating System: Linux Sandbox\\\\n- Terminal:  iTerm2\\\\n\\\\n## Bug Description\\\\nWhenever I install Claude Code for the first time, I get an error with the following stack trace:\\\\n```\\\\nRangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded\\\\n    at new bV1 (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_kuaa/claude-code/cli.js:61:69344)\\\\n    at file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_2ney/claude-code/cli.js:745:62623\\\\n    at Q (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_smci/claude-code/cli.js:674:14418)\\\\n    at file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_zhiu/claude-code/cli.js:745:62924\\\\n    at Q (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_a2ic/claude-code/cli.js:674:14418)\\\\n    at ul4 (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_yudi/claude-code/cli.js:745:63356)\\\\n    at C1 (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_g81c/claude-code/cli.js:745:64689)\\\\n    at kN (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_cgwi/claude-code/cli.js:724:756)\\\\n    at P$2 (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_qs03/claude-code/cli.js:753:2376)\\\\n    at pA (file:///opt/npm/lib/node_modules/@anthropic-ai_dozn/claude-code/cli.js:753:1312)\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nIt's fine the second time though.\\\\n\\\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\\\n1. Install claude-code, e.g. by using the sandbox scripts at https://github.com/Keno/ClaudeBox.jl\\\\n\\\\n## Expected Behavior\\\\nIt launches the first time\\\\n\\\\n## Actual Behavior\\\\nIt errors the first time as above, works the second time.\\\\n\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"has repro\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7g\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:linux\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7w\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:packaging\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYiTA\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":0,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:30Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:30Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017370,\\\"number\\\":11,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Terminal Width Detection Fails in statusLine command\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nI would like to use the current terminal width to right justify the model name in the `statusLine` `command`.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, `$COLUMNS` is not set, and `tput cols` always ruturns 80 when run inside Claude Code.\\\\n\\\\nCan we have the current terminal width made available to that command?\\\\n\\\\nIn case it's not obvious, I'm talking about this in `~/.claude/settings.json`:\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n  \\\\\\\"statusLine\\\\\\\": {\\\\n    \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"~/bin/claudecode-statusline\\\\\\\"\\\\n  }\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: linux\\\\n- Terminal: gnome-terminal\\\\n- Version: 1.0.72\\\\n- Feedback ID: 9bb0af8a-2729-4a68-8de7-e755679f1036\\\\n\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:linux\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7w\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:tui\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfrw\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:25Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:25Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017317,\\\"number\\\":10,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Memory Update Interaction Blocked During Claude Code Execution\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nI am unable to update memories using # when claude is working. Pressing enter appears to have no effect. I can enter normal commands while claude is working, just not memories.\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: darwin\\\\n- Terminal: Apple_Terminal\\\\n- Version: 1.0.62\\\\n- Feedback ID: \\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:macos\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfIw\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:tui\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfrw\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"memory\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYgjA\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:23Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:24Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017253,\\\"number\\\":9,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"[BUG]\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Environment\\\\n- Claude CLI version: 1.0.72\\\\n- Operating System: MacOS 15.5\\\\n- Terminal:  Warp\\\\n\\\\n## Bug Description\\\\n`⏺ Great idea! Let's get our internal code reviewer to take a look before Copilot gets too hungry!\\\\n   🕵️\\\\n\\\\n⏺ code-reviewer(Review migration file)\\\\n  ⎿\\\\n\\\\n✳ Channelling… (38s · ⚒ 1.0k tokens · esc to interrupt)\\\\n\\\\n╭────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\\\\n│ \\\\u003e                                                                                                  │\\\\n╰────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\\\\n  ? for shortcuts\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003c--- Last few GCs ---\\\\u003e\\\\n\\\\n[15609:0x150008000] 60540011 ms: Mark-Compact 3696.1 (4130.1) -\\\\u003e 3683.2 (4138.4) MB, pooled: 0 MB, 925.88 / 0.00 ms  (average mu = 0.406, current mu = 0.321) allocation failure; scavenge might not succeed\\\\n[15609:0x150008000] 60541