iner.json`\\\\n  - `.devcontainer/Dockerfile`\\\\n  - `.devcontainer/init-firewall.sh`\\\\n\\\\n  The `LICENSE.md` file states:\\\\n  \\\\u003e © Anthropic PBC. All rights reserved. Use is subject to Anthropic's [Commercial Terms of Service](https://www.anthropic.com/legal/commercial-terms).\\\\n\\\\n  **Are these devcontainer configuration files also covered by this same license and Commercial Terms of Service?**\\\\n\\\\n  I couldn't find any separate license information for these files specifically, so I wanted to confirm before using them.\\\\n\\\\n  Thank you for the clarification!\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":11413102161,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"question\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"d876e3\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Further information is requested\\\",\\\"default\\\":true,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeUQ\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413103180,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/area:packaging\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:packaging\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYiTA\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":0,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:24:09Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:24:09Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38\\\",\\\"comments_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38/comments\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/38/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAABHoVKbw\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807019133,\\\"number\\\":39,\\\"state\\\":\\\"closed\\\",\\\"state_reason\\\":\\\"completed\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"[DOCS] Slash command frontmatter table is misformatted\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"The [slash command frontmatter docs table](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/slash-commands#frontmatter) is malformed markdown and doesn't display properly. This should be an easy fix.\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":11413102137,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/documentation\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"documentation\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"0075ca\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Improvements or additions to documentation\\\",\\\"default\\\":true,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeOQ\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"closed_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:24:10Z\\\",\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:24:09Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:26:11Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39\\\",\\\"comments_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39/comments\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/39/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAABHoVKfQ\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807023986,\\\"number\\\":40,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"[BUG] MCP reconnection fails with different patterns for direct command vs interactive menu\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Environment\\\\n- Platform (select one):\\\\n  - [x] Anthropic API\\\\n  - [ ] AWS Bedrock\\\\n  - [ ] Google Vertex AI\\\\n  - [ ] Other: \\\\u003c!-- specify --\\\\u003e\\\\n- Claude CLI version: 1.0.71 (Claude Code)\\\\n- Operating System: Linux (WSL2) - 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2\\\\n- Terminal: VSCode integrated terminal\\\\n\\\\n## Bug Description\\\\nTwo different MCP reconnection methods exhibit different failure patterns:\\\\n1. **Direct command** (`/mcp reconnect \\\\u003cserver-name\\\\u003e`): Shows \\\\\\\"Successfully reconnected\\\\\\\" but always disconnects immediately\\\\n2. **Interactive menu** (`/mcp \\\\u003cserver-name\\\\u003e` → Reconnect): Fails on first attempt, succeeds on second attempt\\\\n\\\\nThe issue is reproducible with MCP's official Rust SDK example.\\\\n\\\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\\\n\\\\n### Setup: Build MCP's official Rust SDK counter example\\\\n```bash\\\\n# Clone the official MCP Rust SDK\\\\ngit clone https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/rust-sdk.git /tmp/rust-sdk\\\\ncd /tmp/rust-sdk\\\\n\\\\n# Build the counter example\\\\ncargo build --example servers_counter_stdio\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### Configure Claude Code\\\\nCreate or update `.mcp.json` in your project directory:\\\\n```json\\\\n{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"mcpServers\\\\\\\": {\\\\n    \\\\\\\"counter-test\\\\\\\": {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"cargo\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"args\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"run\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"--manifest-path\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"/tmp/rust-sdk/Cargo.toml\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"--example\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"servers_counter_stdio\\\\\\\"]\\\\n    }\\\\n  }\\\\n}\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### Pattern A: Direct reconnect command\\\\n1. Start Claude Code in the project directory\\\\n2. Initial connection to counter-test succeeds\\\\n3. Use `/mcp reconnect counter-test` to reconnect\\\\n4. Claude Code displays \\\\\\\"Successfully reconnected to counter-test\\\\\\\"\\\\n5. **However, the connection is immediately closed**\\\\n6. Repeat `/mcp reconnect counter-test` multiple times\\\\n7. **All attempts show \\\\\\\"Successfully reconnected\\\\\\\" but immediately disconnect**\\\\n\\\\n### Pattern B: Interactive reconnect via menu\\\\n1. Start Claude Code in the project directory\\\\n2. Initial connection to counter-test succeeds\\\\n3. Use `/mcp counter-test` to open interactive menu\\\\n4. Select \\\\\\\"Reconnect\\\\\\\" option\\\\n5. Claude Code displays \\\\\\\"Reconnected to counter-test.\\\\\\\" (note: different message)\\\\n6. **First reconnection fails silently** (connection is lost)\\\\n7. Repeat `/mcp counter-test` and select \\\\\\\"Reconnect\\\\\\\" again\\\\n8. Second reconnection succeeds and remains stable\\\\n\\\\n## Expected Behavior\\\\nMCP server reconnection should succeed on the first attempt.\\\\n\\\\n## Actual Behavior\\\\n- **Direct command (`/mcp reconnect counter-test`)**: Always shows \\\\\\\"Successfully reconnected to counter-test\\\\\\\" but immediately disconnects\\\\n- **Interactive menu (`/mcp counter-test` → Reconnect)**: First attempt fails silently, second attempt succeeds\\\\n- Different success messages indicate different code paths:\\\\n  - Direct: \\\\\\\"Successfully reconnected to counter-test\\\\\\\" (misleading - connection always fails)\\\\n  - Interactive: \\\\\\\"Reconnected to counter-test.\\\\\\\" (accurate - but only on second attempt)\\\\n- Pattern is 100% reproducible\\\\n\\\\n## Additional Context\\\\n**Workaround**: Use `/mcp counter-test` and select Reconnect from the menu **twice** - the second attempt will succeed.\\\\nThe direct `/mcp reconnect counter-test` command never works and should be avoided.\\\\n\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":11413102134,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/bug\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"d73a4a\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"default\\\":true,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102318,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/has%20repro\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"has repro\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7g\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102319,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/platform:linux\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:linux\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7w\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413103570,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/area:mcp\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:mcp\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYj0g\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":2,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:26:12Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:26:13Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40\\\",\\\"comments_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40/comments\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/40/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAABHoVdcg\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807024063,\\\"number\\\":41,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"After session reset, assistant doesn’t re-request directory permission on first attempt; bash path is blocked without triggering interactive permission flow\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Environment**\\\\n- WSL2 Ubuntu 24.04 (kernel 6.6.x)\\\\n- Default user: `yang`\\\\n- Start directory (cwd) when launching the CLI: `/mnt/c/Users/yang`\\\\n- Tool: Claude Code CLI (reproduced with Opus 4.1 and Sonnet 4)\\\\n- Reproduces after model switch or `wsl --shutdown` (session reset)\\\\n\\\\n**Problem summary**\\\\nAfter a session reset, the chat context continues but the execution sandbox (and its per-session whitelist) is reset. On the *first* attempt to access a non-whitelisted path, the assistant often assumes it still has access and sends a bash `ls` that gets blocked. Crucially, it does **not** immediately trigger the interactive permission request (e.g., “Add as a working directory”). Only after a subsequent/altered request does the assistant switch to the flow that prompts the user to add the path. This creates a perception gap: the model doesn’t realize the environment requires re-authorization.\\\\n\\\\n**Steps to Reproduce**\\\\n1) Reset: `wsl --shutdown`, reopen WSL. Ensure `pwd` = `/mnt/c/Users/yang`.\\\\n2) Ask the assistant in natural language to view `/home/yang` (e.g., “List /home/yang” / “Check /home/yang”).\\\\n3) Observed behavior (first attempt):\\\\n   - Assistant issues a bash `ls /home/yang`.\\\\n   - It’s blocked with:\\\\n     \\\\u003e For security, Claude Code may only list files in the allowed working directories for this session: '/mnt/c/Users/yang'.\\\\n   - No interactive prompt to add `/home/yang` appears.\\\\n4) Ask the same again (or phrase slightly differently). Now an interactive prompt may appear:\\\\n   - “Add /home/yang as a working directory for this session”.\\\\n   - Choose to add → subsequent `ls /home/yang` succeeds.\\\\n5) Repeat from step 1: behavior repeats (first attempt after reset = no prompt; later attempt = prompt).\\\\n\\\\n**Expected behavior**\\\\n- On the **first** blocked access after a session reset, the assistant/tooling should recognize the whitelist miss and immediately trigger the interactive permission request (or surface a clear “Add as working directory” affordance). Ideally the router treats this as a deterministic fallback, not dependent on phrasing or retries.\\\\n\\\\n**Actual behavior**\\\\n- First attempt after reset: bash path gets hard-blocked with a custom message and **no** interactive request UI.\\\\n- Only on a subsequent attempt/alternative route does the assistant prompt to add the path, which then works.\\\\n\\\\n**Why this matters (UX)**\\\\n- Chat continuity suggests state is preserved, but execution permissions were reset; the assistant doesn’t reflect that, leading to confusion and extra retries. Users perceive it as the model “thinking it still has permission”.\\\\n\\\\n**Suggested improvements**\\\\n1) Router: on whitelist block, auto-trigger interactive permission request for the specific path; show a clear button in the error UI.\\\\n2) Structured errors (e.g., `ERR_NOT_WHITELISTED path=/home/yang can_request=true`) so the assistant can reliably switch flows on the *first* attempt.\\\\n3) Startup banner after reset: “Permissions reset. Allowed: …”.\\\\n4) `/status` command to list/manage allowed directories; optional per-project defaults (e.g., `/home/yang`).\\\\n\\\\n**Notes / Screenshots**\\\\n- Before adding: allowed = `'/mnt/c/Users/yang'`\\\\n- After prompt: allowed = `'/mnt/c/Users/yang', '/home/yang'`\\\\n- Screenshots attached: (1) first blocked attempt w/o prompt; (2) later prompt to add directory.\\\\n\\\\n**问题概述**\\\\n会话重置后（例如 `wsl --shutdown` 或切换模型），聊天上下文还在，但执行沙箱与其“会话级白名单”被清零。首次访问非白名单路径时，助手常常“以为自己还有权限”，先发出 bash `ls`，被拦后也**没有**立刻弹出“加入工作目录”的交互。只有第二次/换个说法后，才出现授权弹窗。用户观感是：模型并没有意识到需要“重新申请权限”。\\\\n\\\\n**期望**\\\\n- 在会话重置后的**第一次**阻拦上，就能自动触发交互式授权（或在错误 UI 中提供明显的“加入白名单”入口），而不是要靠用户重复/改述来触发。\\\\n\\\\n**改进建议**\\\\n- 见英文部分的 1–4 条（自动降级、结构化错误、启动提示、/status 管理）。\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":11413102134,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/bug\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"d73a4a\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"default\\\":true,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102318,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/has%20repro\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"has repro\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7g\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102319,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/platform:linux\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:linux\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7w\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102423,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/area:tools\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:tools\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfVw\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":11413102495,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/labels/area:security\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:security\\\",\\\"color\\\":\\\"ededed\\\",\\\"default\\\":false,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfnw\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":0,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:26:13Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:26:13Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41\\\",\\\"comments_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41/comments\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/claude-code/issues/41/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAABHoVdvw\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807024087,\\\"number\\\":42,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Clipboard Image Paste Functionality Broken on Mac Terminal\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nThe ctrl-v shortcut no longer pastes images into Claude Code as of this morning.I'm uing Webstorm on a Mac but it doesnt work in any terminal environment now. When I press ctrl-v I now get text instead of an image. I've restarted my Mac and it hasn't helped. AFAIK I've not changed any settings to bring this about\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: darwin\\\\n- Terminal: webstorm\\\\n- Version: 1.0.71\\\\n- Feedb