      "result": "{\"meta\": null, \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\\"issues\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":4807017370,\\\"number\\\":11,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Terminal Width Detection Fails in statusLine command\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nI would like to use the current terminal width to right justify the model name in the `statusLine` `command`.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, `$COLUMNS` is not set, and `tput cols` always ruturns 80 when run inside Claude Code.\\\\n\\\\nCan we have the current terminal width made available to that command?\\\\n\\\\nIn case it's not obvious, I'm talking about this in `~/.claude/settings.json`:\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n  \\\\\\\"statusLine\\\\\\\": {\\\\n    \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"~/bin/claudecode-statusline\\\\\\\"\\\\n  }\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: linux\\\\n- Terminal: gnome-terminal\\\\n- Version: 1.0.72\\\\n- Feedback ID: 9bb0af8a-2729-4a68-8de7-e755679f1036\\\\n\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYeNg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:linux\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYe7w\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:tui\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTNEKgM8AAAACqEYfrw\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:25Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T00:23:25Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4807017587,\\\"number\\\":14,\\\"state\\\":\\\"OPEN\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"[BUG] Maximum call stack size exceeded on first install\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Environment\\\\n- Platform (select one):\\\\n  - [x] Anthropic API\\\\n  - [ ] AWS Bedrock\\\\n  - [ ] Google Vertex AI\\\\n  - [ ] Other: \\\\u003c!-- specify --\\\\u003e\\\\n- Claude CLI version: 1.0.72 (Claude Code)\\\\n- Operating System: Linux Sandbox\\\\