      "branch": "feat/label-color-guide",
      "content": "# Label Organization Guide\n\nThis label documentation provides a central label guide for repository organization, visual organization, and issue triage.\n\n## Label Categories\n\n| Label Name | Category | Description |\n|------------|----------|-------------|\n| `bug` | issue-type | Reports something that is not working as expected. |\n| `documentation` | issue-type | Requests or changes related to documentation improvements. |\n| `duplicate` | status | Marks an issue or pull request that already exists elsewhere. |\n| `enhancement` | issue-type | Proposes a new feature, improvement, or request. |\n| `external` | status | Tracks issues caused by, blocked by, or primarily involving external systems. |\n| `has repro` | status | Indicates the issue includes enough reproduction details to investigate. |\n| `memory` | area | Identifies issues related to memory behavior, retention, or saved context. |\n| `perf:memory` | performance | Tracks memory-related performance problems or optimizations. |\n| `question` | issue-type | Requests information, clarification, or support rather than a code change. |\n| `area:api` | area | Covers API request, response, serialization, and integration behavior. |\n| `area:auth` | area | Covers authentication, login, credential, token, and account access behavior. |\n| `area:core` | area | Covers core Claude Code behavior, session handling, and central runtime logic. |\n| `area:ide` | area | Covers IDE integrations and editor-specific workflows. |\n| `area:mcp` | area | Covers Model Context Protocol integrations, tools, and server behavior. |\n| `area:model` | area | Covers model interaction, output quality, and model-facing behavior. |\n| `area:packaging` | area | Covers installation, packaging, release artifacts, and distribution behavior. |\n| `area:security` | area | Covers permissions, sandboxing, policy, and security-sensitive behavior. |\n| `area:tools` | area | Covers built-in tool behavior, tool routing, hooks, and tool execution. |\n| `area:tui` | area | Covers terminal UI, keyboard handling, status line, display, and terminal interaction. |\n| `platform:linux` | platform | Applies to issues reproduced on Linux or Linux-like environments. |\n| `platform:macos` | platform | Applies to issues reproduced on macOS or Darwin environments. |\n| `platform:windows` | platform | Applies to issues reproduced on Windows environments. |\n\n## Usage Guidelines\n\n- Use issue-type labels (`bug`, `documentation`, `enhancement`, `question`) to describe the primary kind of work or report.\n- Use platform labels (`platform:linux`, `platform:macos`, `platform:windows`) when behavior is specific to an operating system or terminal environment.\n- Use area labels (`area:*` and `memory`) to identify the component, subsystem, or workflow affected by the issue or pull request.\n- Use status labels (`duplicate`, `external`, `has repro`) to communicate triage state, ownership boundaries, or investigation readiness.\n- Use performance labels (`perf:*`) when the issue is specifically about resource usage, speed, or scalability.\n- Prefer combining one issue-type label with the most specific area and platform labels so visual organization remains clear and triage is easier.\n",
      "message": "Add label organization guide",
