    "input": {
      "base": "main",
      "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds label documentation in a centralized organization guide so contributors can understand the repository label categories and use them for better visual improvement and issue triage. This documentation supports label documentation, visual organization, and consistent repository organization.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added `docs/LABEL_COLORS.md` as the label organization guide.\n- Documented every existing repository label with its category and description.\n- Added usage guidance for issue-type, platform, area, status, and performance labels.\n- Linked the documentation work back to the label guide tracking issue.\n\nFixes #54\n\n## Verification\n\nAll labels have been documented in the label organization guide, and the table includes every existing repository label.\n\nKeywords: label documentation, organization guide, visual improvement, documentation",
      "draft": false,
      "head": "feat/label-color-guide",
      "maintainer_can_modify": true,
